<body>
<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>A <rs type="material">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">altar-stele</rs>, with very simple moulding above and below on three sides (<measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.84</measure> x <measure dim="width" type="length" unit="metre">0.395</measure> x <measure dim="depth" type="length" unit="metre">0.32</measure>). There is no trace of carving on the face, which probably carried a painted image.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p>Inscribed on the upper moulding (l.1) and at the top of the face (l.2).</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>standard forms: l.1 <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.015</measure>-<measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.02</measure>; l.2, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.02</measure>; ΗΝ in ligature</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0101" notAfter="0300" exact="none">Second to third centuries A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)
</p>
</div>
<div type="edition" lang="grc">
<head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Ποδηνέμος">Ποδηνέ<unclear reason="damage">μ</unclear>ος</name></persName> <w lemma="πάλος">πάλου</w> <num value="3">γ</num> <w lemma="ὑπό">ὑπ<supplied reason="lost">ὸ</supplied></w>  <lb n="2"/> <persName type="aphrodisian"><name reg="Ἑρμᾶς" type="">Ἑρμᾶ</name></persName> <space extent="unknown"/> <w lemma="πάλος">πάλου</w> <num value="4">δ</num> </ab>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Podenemos of brigade 3 by Hermas of brigade 4.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>The name is a conjecture by Reinach, and not certain.</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p> <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Necropolis, South-east</rs> outside the south-east gate (Gaudin); in the same area, but below ground level in 1976.</rs>
<rs type="origLocation">Unknown</rs>
<rs type="lastLocation">Museum</rs>
</p>
</div>
